
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "HimachalPradesh";
}
<link href="~/Script/StatesCss/himachal.css" rel="stylesheet" />
<div class="main-container">
    <!-- BACKGROUND IMAGE -->
    <div id="top-section-main">

        <div id="top-section-content">
            <h1> Kaza </h1>
            <h2> Himachal Pradesh </h2>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- PLACES TO VISIT SECTION -->
    <div id="feature-section">
        <h1 class="feature-section-title"> The top places to visit in <i>Himachal Pradesh</i></h1>
        <div class="feature-content">
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/HimachalPradesh/manali.jpg">
                <h3> Manali </h3>
                <p>  Manali captivates you with its snow-capped mountains and impressive views. Manali is one of the most beautiful places to visit in Himachal.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/HimachalPradesh/kasol.jpg">
                <h3> Kasol</h3>
                <p> Kasol looks like a perfect picture come to life. It is slowly gaining massive popularity as one of the most popular tourist places in Himachal Pradesh and is a base camp for moderate treks in the state.  </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/HimachalPradesh/spiti.jpg">
                <h3> Spiti </h3>
                <p> One of the hidden beauties of North India is the Spiti Valley. Spiti Valley is a snow cladded desert mountain located high in the Himalayas in the north-eastern state of Himachal Pradesh.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/HimachalPradesh/tirthan.jpg">
                <h3> Tirthan Valley </h3>
                <p>  Tirthan Valley is one of popular places to visit in Himachal Pradesh. The valley is immensely beautiful, it gives you a chance to witness a beautiful rainbow or brown trout in the glacial waters.  </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- MAP SECTION -->
    <div id="showcase1-container">
        <div class="showcase">
            <div class="cols-2">
                <iframe class="showcase1-pic" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3472280.155078479!2d75.05076823358746!3d31.800513634581954!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x390453c367f901f7%3A0x7cfe04c5564b7725!2sHimachal%20Pradesh!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1618243364792!5m2!1sen!2sin" width="600" height="450" style="border:0;" allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy"></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-2">
                <div class="feature-text">
                    <h1 class="section-title">
                        Facts of Himachal <div style="padding-left:50px;"> Pradesh </div>
                    </h1>
                    <p class="section-content">
                        <ul class="section-content-list">
                            <li>
                                Out of the total population of Himachal Pradesh, about 90% lives in rural areas.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Occupying around 25%, Shimla district has the largest urban population of the state.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                As per the CMS – India Corruption Study 2017, Himachal Pradesh is the least corrupt state of India.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                As of October 2009, the state has imposed a complete ban on production, storage, use, sale and distribution of all types of polythene bags made of non-biodegradable material.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Imposing a ban on tobacco, Himachal Pradesh became the first smoke free state of India, as of July 2013.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- LAST SECTION -->
    <div id="call-to-action">
        <div class="showcase">
            <div class="cols-1">
                <h1 class="action-title">
                    What are you waiting for??
                </h1>
                <p style="line-height:1.2em;">
                    Book your tickets, pack your bags and
                    Get.. Set.. GO!!
                    If winter is your season, then Himachal Pradesh is your state and it is waiting for you!!
                </p>
                <P>
                    <a href="#" class="BookHotelBtn"> BOOK A HOTEL TODAY!! </a>
                </P>
                <div class="text"> <p style="color: white; margin-top:10px; font-weight: 1000; font-style:italic;"> Shimla - Himachal Pradesh </p></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
